<item>
            <title>[MATH-422] Constructor calls overrideable methods</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MATH-422</link>
                <project id="12310485" key="MATH">Commons Math</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The ctor MicrosphereInterpolator(int microsphereElements, int brightnessExponent) calls 2 public setters that are not final.&lt;br/&gt;
This is unsafe if the class is ever extended.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Likewise for ComplexFormat(String imaginaryCharacter, NumberFormat realFormat,  NumberFormat imaginaryFormat)&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Are the setters even needed?&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
